# Build context for the app image is the repo root (the web build needs the
# workspace packages @tenir/client-core + @tenir/contract, and the api stage
# needs api/). Keep the context lean: drop installed deps, VCS/CI metadata, and
# everything the image build never reads.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.vite
**/coverage
.git
.github
.claude
.venv
.venv-work
**/__pycache__
api/tests
docs
docker-compose.yml
# NOTE: schema.sql is intentionally NOT ignored — the api image bakes it in
# (api/Dockerfile) and applies it idempotently on Postgres pool open, so an
# existing data dir gains additively-added tables (e.g. `cues`). Postgres only
# runs schema.sql on a fresh volume, so it can't be excluded from the context.
scripts
litellm
.env.example
*.log
